00:50:32.020 --> 00:50:37.110
who don't know carbon sequestration is, I
should make it very clear. It's capturing

00:50:37.110 --> 00:50:43.740
the CO2 gases out of the smokestack of a coal
plant, most of the time. You can do it on

00:50:43.740 --> 00:50:46.420
other types of things, but capturing CO2,
compressing into a super critical liquid and

00:50:46.420 --> 00:50:52.000
then pumping it underground into deep storage,
usually in saline aquifers that are way down

00:50:52.000 --> 00:50:57.690
several thousand feet below surface. And presumably,
if you do it in the right place, and these

00:50:57.690 --> 00:51:03.610
aquifers are in stable geologic systems that
we understand well, it will be locked up down

00:51:03.610 --> 00:51:09.680
there for a long time, you'll reduce-- so
